#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Paṭhamavagga → āyuvaggo (bj) | āyuvaggo paṭhamo (pts2)
msgctxt "sn4.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Life Span"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Tapokammasutta"
msgstr "1. Mortification"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.103"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.231"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre "
"ajapālanigrodhamūle paṭhamābhisambuddho."
msgstr ""
"At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā "
"at the root of the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River."

msgctxt "sn4.1:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavato rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr "Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind:"

msgctxt "sn4.1:1.4"
msgid "“mutto vatamhi tāya dukkarakārikāya."
msgstr "“I am truly freed from that grueling work!"

msgctxt "sn4.1:1.5"
msgid "Sādhu mutto vatamhi tāya anatthasaṃhitāya dukkarakārikāya."
msgstr "Thank goodness I’m freed from that pointless grueling work."

# I follow BB in adopting Bj reading; it is the Lectio difficilior
#. VAR: Sādhu vatamhi mutto bodhiṃ samajjhagan”ti → sādhu ṭhito sato bodhiṃ samajjhaganti (bj, pts1-2) | sādhu vatamhi satto bodhisamajjhagūti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.6"
msgid "Sādhu vatamhi mutto bodhiṃ samajjhagan”ti."
msgstr "Thank goodness that, steadfast and mindful, I have attained awakening.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.1:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"And then Māra the Wicked, knowing what the Buddha was thinking, went up to "
"him and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.232"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.1"
msgid "“Tapokammā apakkamma,"
msgstr "“You’ve departed from the practice of mortification"

# Read yena, duh.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.2"
msgid "ye na sujjhanti māṇavā;"
msgstr "by which humans purify themselves."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.3"
msgid "Asuddho maññasi suddho,"
msgstr "You’re impure, but think yourself pure;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: suddhimaggā aparaddho → suddhimaggamaparaddho (bj, pts1-2) | suddhimaggaṃ aparaddho (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.4"
msgid "suddhimaggā aparaddho”ti."
msgstr "you’ve strayed from the path of purity.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.1:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.1"
msgid "“Anatthasaṃhitaṃ ñatvā,"
msgstr "“I realized that it’s pointless;"

# This phrase occurs thrice. here, Thag 3.1, and Snp.252 at Snp 3.2. There we have “Ye vāpi loke amarā bahū tapā” which I can’t help feeling would make better sense if amara meant “endless”. However, i will retain the accepted meaning.
#. <br>
#. VAR: amaraṃ tapaṃ → aparaṃ tapaṃ (s1-3, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.2"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci amaraṃ tapaṃ;"
msgstr "all that mortification in search of immortality"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.3"
msgid "Sabbaṃ natthāvahaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "is as futile"

# See BB for readings.
#. <br>
#. VAR: dhammani → dhammaniṃ (pts1) | phiyārittaṃ vajahmani (pts2) | jammaniṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.4"
msgid "phiyārittaṃva dhammani."
msgstr "as oars and rudder on dry land."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.1"
msgid "Sīlaṃ samādhi paññañca,"
msgstr "Ethics, immersion, and wisdom:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.2"
msgid "Maggaṃ bodhāya bhāvayaṃ;"
msgstr "by developing this path to awakening"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.3"
msgid "Pattosmi paramaṃ suddhiṃ,"
msgstr "I attained ultimate purity."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.4"
msgid "Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti."
msgstr "You’re defeated, terminator!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.1:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti, dukkhī "
"dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!”"
" miserable and sad, vanished right there."
